1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,667
<i>I'm really going to tell
Ma'am Regina</i>

2
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,233
<i> that Sir Greg is cheating.</i>

3
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:16,567
<i> I hope we can still fix this.</i>

4
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Please don't be mad at me.</i>

5
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:21,233
<i>- I really like you.
- Same goes with Ma'am Marj.</i>

6
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:25,200
<i>- You're going to interfere?
- Yes. I'm stepping in.</i>

7
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:26,867
<i> Mom, are you okay?</i>

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,300
<i> How can I be okay</i>

9
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:31,967
<i>when I just found out
my husband is cheating again?</i>

10
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:33,833
<i> Did you catch him?</i>

11
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,633
Mom, get up!

12
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:21,800
Get out of there!

13
00:01:21,933 --> 00:01:22,800
Mom!

14
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:23,967
What are you doing?

15
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,633
Marj, Marj...

16
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:28,667
Marj...

17
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:30,433
- What...
- I didn't mean it, Marj.

18
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:32,400
Sorry, Marj.

19
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:34,633
Let me explain.

20
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:46,933
- Come on!
- We were just talking.

21
00:01:47,067 --> 00:01:49,367
It didn't mean anything.

22
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:50,733
"Just talking"?

23
00:01:50,867 --> 00:01:53,700
In the bedroom? On the bed?

24
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:56,433
Half-naked?

25
00:01:56,567 --> 00:01:58,433
That's Marj!

26
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:00,900
What if the kids saw you?

27
00:02:01,033 --> 00:02:05,100
Or worse, Paolo's mom?
Come on, Mom!

28
00:02:05,233 --> 00:02:07,100
- Let's go!
- Evelyn!

29
00:02:08,033 --> 00:02:09,367
Evelyn!

30
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:12,833
And Dad.

31
00:02:19,133 --> 00:02:21,500
Come inside.
Get inside the room!

32
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:27,033
Honey, please forgive me.
I just got carried away.

33
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:28,700
What? You got carried away?

34
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:33,000
If you caught Dad like that,
would you just accept it?

35
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,733
You always told me
how miserable you were

36
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:40,400
when you caught Dad
with another woman.

37
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:41,567
That you couldn't accept it.

38
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,667
And now you're messing around
with a married man?

39
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,567
Paolo's dad, of all people?

40
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:48,933
I didn't mean for this
to happen.

41
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:54,500
I just fell easily when
Greg started sweet-talking me.

42
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:58,833
He made me feel special.

43
00:02:58,967 --> 00:03:02,933
I got overwhelmed by...

44
00:03:03,067 --> 00:03:07,033
- my loneliness.
- I don't get it, Mom!

45
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:10,033
I wish you'd think about others,
not just yourself.

46
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:12,300
Don't you feel sorry for me?

47
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:14,167
My child has cancer.

48
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:18,267
My marriage is already falling
apart, and now this?

49
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:21,833
Weren't you and Paolo's mom
getting along?

50
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,067
You didn't just betray
Paolo and me.

51
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,400
You betrayed her even more.

52
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,967
What the hell were you thinking,
Mom?

53
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:33,400
Marj...

54
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,700
Can you not make a scene?

55
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:39,567
You're just going to make things
worse if someone hears you.

56
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Your mom and I are both adults.

57
00:03:44,067 --> 00:03:47,167
Stay out of it.
Just forget what you saw, okay?

58
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,000
Easy for you to say

59
00:03:49,133 --> 00:03:51,833
because you don't care
about how anyone feels,

60
00:03:51,967 --> 00:03:53,967
especially your wife.

61
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:58,700
Enough. Do not test my patience.

62
00:03:58,833 --> 00:04:00,633
Maybe you've forgotten.

63
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:03,200
You're under my roof.

64
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,000
Maybe you've forgotten.

65
00:04:05,133 --> 00:04:08,967
I saw how you were seducing
my mom.

66
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:12,100
That's never happening again.

67
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:13,833
Do you understand me?

68
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:15,867
Come on, Mom.

69
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,933
Stop.

70
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:21,000
Greg, please, don't hurt Marj.

71
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:23,600
Let go of me! I'll tell Paolo!

72
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:26,733
Go ahead.

73
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:32,300
You think he'll be surprised?
Mad?

74
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:36,300
This isn't the first time
I've cheated on Regina.

75
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:42,533
Everyone in this
house knows it.

76
00:04:42,667 --> 00:04:46,000
And they don't have a choice
but to accept it.

77
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:49,300
You know why?

78
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:51,967
Because I have them
all under my thumb.

79
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:55,567
And you?

80
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,467
Have you thought

81
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:00,600
about how Paolo would feel

82
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:03,567
if you told him
about what your mom and I did?

83
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:11,100
He might think Evelyn
went after me for the money.

84
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:12,467
For comfort.

85
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:18,333
Paolo wouldn't
do that to me.

86
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:21,000
He might not say it...

87
00:05:21,133 --> 00:05:25,367
but we both know he'll think it.

88
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:29,033
Do you really think
he'll forgive your mom

89
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:33,700
for ruining my relationship
with his mother?

90
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,667
You go check on that.

91
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,967
I'm heading back to our room.

92
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:47,367
Be careful.
Someone might see you.

93
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:58,700
Think long and hard before
you do something you'll regret.

94
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:04,333
Do you think your
husband's that understanding?

95
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:06,267
He will loathe you, Marj!

96
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,333
Every time he looks at you,

97
00:06:10,467 --> 00:06:14,200
he'll see
what your mom and I did.

98
00:06:16,933 --> 00:06:19,067
Are you really going to let
your marriage fall apart

99
00:06:20,433 --> 00:06:22,600
just because of your conscience?

100
00:06:32,733 --> 00:06:34,467
What's going on here?

101
00:06:46,433 --> 00:06:49,367
I was just taking Mom
back to her room.

102
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,933
She got lost.

103
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:54,200
We ran into Dad.

104
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,067
Then...

105
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,867
why did I hear yelling?

106
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:03,433
They got startled. Mom screamed.

107
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:07,067
So I pulled them in here,
so the kids wouldn't wake up.

108
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:12,133
Really? Because it sounded like
people were fighting.

109
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:16,300
How about you? Where were you?

110
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:23,033
Oh, I just went to the study.
Sent some important emails.

111
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:28,933
Come on. Let's go to bed.

112
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:30,267
Let's go.

113
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:36,967
Dad.

114
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,133
Good night.

115
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:41,067
Good night.

116
00:07:58,133 --> 00:07:59,833
Are you okay?

117
00:07:59,967 --> 00:08:01,900
You're unusually quiet.

118
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:03,200
Just tired.

119
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:05,833
Waking up in the middle
of the night messes me up.

120
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:11,100
How about you?
It's past midnight.

121
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:15,900
Why'd you go downstairs to work?
Couldn't it wait until morning?

122
00:08:17,367 --> 00:08:19,700
I couldn't sleep.

123
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:24,433
And the email was urgent.
Other departments needed it.

124
00:08:26,533 --> 00:08:28,667
Are you sure you're okay?

125
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,267
Because you don't look like it.

126
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:39,033
I'm just stressed and tired
from taking care of Jasmine.

127
00:08:40,533 --> 00:08:41,733
Okay.

128
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:43,967
Well...

129
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:46,500
If you need to tell me
anything...

130
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:48,133
Yeah, yeah, I will, love.

131
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:20,200
<i> I hope we can still fix this.</i>

132
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:23,967
<i>Please don't be mad at me.
I really like you.</i>

133
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:39,867
I'll start eating.

134
00:10:40,533 --> 00:10:42,167
Eat slowly, Jobert.

135
00:10:44,867 --> 00:10:49,300
Marj! Let's eat, breakfast.
It's good.

136
00:10:49,433 --> 00:10:51,700
Ma'am Marj,
we have omelet and sausage.

137
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:53,333
Please eat first.

138
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:55,367
Oh, no need to go through
the trouble, Manang.

139
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,400
Sorry, Jobert,
I don't feel like eating today.

140
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:05,000
Marj.

141
00:11:05,133 --> 00:11:09,200
Please don't drag Jobert
into our fight.

142
00:11:12,033 --> 00:11:15,100
Mom, I'm not dragging him
into it.

143
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,200
I'm just being honest
with what I feel.

144
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,667
Manang Yolly?

145
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:21,867
- Yes?
- Weng?

146
00:11:22,233 --> 00:11:25,367
Can I have some? Just a little.

147
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,000
Hey, wait.

148
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:28,933
Please, just a little.

149
00:11:29,067 --> 00:11:30,867
- No, Jobert.
- Dear.

150
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:35,433
Just a little, please.
Just a little.

151
00:11:35,567 --> 00:11:37,400
Jobert...

152
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:38,967
Come on, Jobert.

153
00:11:39,100 --> 00:11:42,700
Jobert, you shouldn't take
something that isn't yours.

154
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:45,833
Especially when you know it
already belongs to someone else.

155
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:51,467
But I will just get a share.
Pong likes vegetables.

156
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,700
Jobert, sharing is different
from taking.

157
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,367
Remember that.

158
00:11:56,633 --> 00:11:58,700
If you take something
meant for someone else,

159
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:01,067
you're not just stealing
from them.

160
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:04,267
You're also losing
your self-respect.

161
00:12:06,733 --> 00:12:08,233
Please, say sorry.

162
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,267
Sorry, Marj.

163
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:15,100
Sorry, Manang Yolly.

164
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:16,633
Sorry, Weng.

165
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:18,733
- It's okay, Jobert.
- It's okay.

166
00:12:18,867 --> 00:12:21,767
All right,
I'll just eat next time, okay?

167
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:26,800
Marj...

168
00:12:26,933 --> 00:12:31,733
What should I do for you
to forgive me?

169
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:33,767
I don't know, Mom.

170
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:36,633
I thought you were different
from Dad.

171
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:39,200
Turns out, you're just the same.

172
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:41,900
You care more about your own
pleasure than our family.

173
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:05,233
Evelyn...

174
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:06,900
let's talk.

175
00:13:07,033 --> 00:13:09,633
Greg, can you just leave
me alone?

176
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:12,833
Come on.

177
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:19,667
Come on, Evelyn.
Don't worry about Marj.

178
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,433
I already convinced her
last night.

179
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,267
She's not going to expose us.

180
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:26,933
Here.

181
00:13:36,533 --> 00:13:38,633
Accept my peace offering.

182
00:13:48,267 --> 00:13:52,067
You really have no shame, Greg.

183
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:53,433
Why?

184
00:13:53,733 --> 00:13:55,467
What do you think?

185
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:58,767
There's nothing wrong
with what happened between us?

186
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:01,667
Let's not add to our sins, Greg.

187
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:07,233
So, can you please stop
what you're doing to me?

188
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:09,333
Will you please calm down?

189
00:14:09,467 --> 00:14:11,167
Evelyn, you're overreacting

190
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:13,200
- just like your daughter.
- Let go of me.

191
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:14,900
Greg, let go...

192
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:17,167
Evelyn, trust me.

193
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:19,367
We can fix this.

194
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:23,033
Greg, let go of me.

195
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:26,600
I regret everything.
I regret being impulsive.

196
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:29,400
I regret giving in to you.

197
00:14:29,567 --> 00:14:32,767
But I know this can't happen.

198
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:34,233
So stop!

199
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:35,800
Just stop! I'm done!

200
00:14:35,933 --> 00:14:37,367
Evelyn...

201
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,167
Don't be so dramatic.

202
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:42,300
We both know you want this, too.

203
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:44,067
Do something for yourself
for once.

204
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:46,100
Not just for your kids.

205
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,067
- Enough, let's end this!
- Mom!

206
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:50,200
- Let go of me!
- Mom!

207
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:52,433
- Mom!
- Evelyn!

208
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:56,000
Let her go! Let go of my mom!

209
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,067
I'm still talking
to your mother.

210
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:03,567
Move away.

211
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:04,700
No!

212
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:05,800
Get out, Jobert!

213
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:08,467
Out!

214
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:13,800
Don't you dare hurt my child!

215
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:17,200
Get out! Leave us alone!

216
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:20,167
- Get out of here!
- You don't have to push me.

217
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:21,433
I know my way out.

218
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:51,933
Mom,

219
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,300
did Uncle Greg hurt you?

220
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:58,733
Did Good Brother's dad fight
you?

221
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:01,233
No, no, Jobert.

222
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:02,467
No.

223
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,533
I'm okay, son.

224
00:16:04,667 --> 00:16:06,333
It's nothing.

225
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:09,533
Just let me be. I'm fine, dear.

226
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,667
Why are you crying?

227
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:15,967
Is it because you and Marj
are fighting?

228
00:16:16,233 --> 00:16:18,333
Why are you fighting?

229
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:22,633
It's because of me.

230
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:26,167
I was being difficult, sweetie.

231
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:31,167
Everything I do is wrong.

232
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:36,833
If you made a mistake,
then say sorry.

233
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:42,633
So sis won't be mad,
and she'll love you again.

234
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:48,700
You're right, Jobert.

235
00:16:55,433 --> 00:16:58,100
I wonder what
they're really fighting about.

236
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:01,467
Could it have something to do

237
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,800
with Ma'am Evelyn's
mysterious boyfriend?

238
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,667
Hey, Oscar, fess up.

239
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:17,433
Was it you?

240
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,667
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
What's going on, Oscar?

241
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,767
You even messed with
Ma'am Evelyn, too?

242
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:26,267
You know what?
You really are something else.

243
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:28,100
Wait, why me?
I had nothing to do with that.

244
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:30,867
Why am I the one being blamed?

245
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,500
Can you blame those two
when you dated both of them?

246
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:36,267
Still surprised?

247
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,633
Manang, seriously...

248
00:17:37,767 --> 00:17:42,433
Oscar, guys like you flirt
with any woman.

249
00:17:42,567 --> 00:17:44,667
Exactly!

250
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:47,300
And now you get to judge, huh?

251
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:53,067
Tell Sir Paolo and Sir Greg.
They're players, too, you know.

252
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,400
I'm really going to tell
Ma'am Regina

253
00:17:56,633 --> 00:17:58,067
that Sir Greg is cheating.

254
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,100
Same goes for Ma'am Marj.

255
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:02,333
Manang Yolly, really?
You're going to get involved?

256
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:04,733
Of course. I'm a woman.

257
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:07,267
I know how painful it
is to be cheated on.

258
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:10,500
We're supposed to have
each other's backs.

259
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:14,333
So yeah, I'm stepping in.

260
00:18:14,467 --> 00:18:16,100
I agree.

261
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:18,367
I'm on your side.

262
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:19,733
And you, finish your food.

263
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,533
Can't you see the dishes
are already being washed?

264
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:25,833
Nurse Daisy, send me the
pictures once you get them.

265
00:18:26,133 --> 00:18:27,167
So I can see them, too.

266
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,233
And message me. Thanks.

267
00:18:29,367 --> 00:18:30,700
Sure, Ma'am.
I'll take care of it.

268
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:42,767
Mom, are you okay?

269
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:48,933
How can I be okay

270
00:18:51,267 --> 00:18:54,700
when I just found out
my husband is cheating again?

271
00:18:57,433 --> 00:18:59,200
You caught him?

272
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:09,133
I saw an...

273
00:19:09,267 --> 00:19:14,033
expensive gift
among Greg's things.

274
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:17,467
From the same jewelry store
he buys from whenever...

275
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,700
he's got a new girl on the side.

276
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:29,100
And he even said, "I like you."

277
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:32,933
Can you imagine?

278
00:19:34,733 --> 00:19:36,767
I can't even...

279
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:41,833
I can't remember the last time
he said that to me.

280
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,600
Mom...

281
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:50,300
He's got no shame!

282
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:54,633
Mom, it's okay. Just let it out.

283
00:19:58,900 --> 00:20:01,367
I'm so sorry
you had to see me this way.

284
00:20:03,533 --> 00:20:05,500
But thank you
for not judging me.

285
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:09,333
I had no right.

286
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,567
You know, Marj,

287
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:15,133
being friends with your mom

288
00:20:15,267 --> 00:20:19,600
made me realize I shouldn't
judge others so quickly.

289
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:24,900
So I want to apologize

290
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:29,167
for how I've treated you
all these years.

291
00:20:30,767 --> 00:20:33,933
Ever since you stepped foot
into this house,

292
00:20:35,533 --> 00:20:38,500
I should have been
a better mother-in-law to you.

293
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:45,133
So, Marj, can we start over?

294
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:50,833
I promise I'll be better.

295
00:20:50,967 --> 00:20:53,167
I promise.

296
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,600
I'm sorry, Marj.

297
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:15,900
- Mom...
- Jobert?

298
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:19,433
Jobert, sweetie,
I brought you ice cream.

299
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:22,333
- Manang Yolly.
- Have a snack first.

300
00:21:22,467 --> 00:21:24,700
Oh, you're going to love this.

301
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:27,300
Chocolate ice cream.

302
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:29,800
- Yeah. Here it is. I know.
- My favorite.

303
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:31,667
- You'll like it.
- Chocolate ice cream.

304
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:35,400
- Go on and eat.
- Thank you, Manang Yolly.

305
00:21:35,533 --> 00:21:37,033
Here's the spoon.

306
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,900
Hey, what's this?

307
00:21:43,067 --> 00:21:45,167
A present?

308
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:46,400
Yes.

309
00:21:46,733 --> 00:21:50,133
Good Brother's dad
gave it to Mom.

310
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:51,233
What?

311
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:55,067
His gift for Mom.

312
00:22:01,367 --> 00:22:03,000
So good!

313
00:22:46,633 --> 00:22:47,933
Mom.

314
00:22:52,533 --> 00:22:53,633
Marj.

315
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:56,933
Please, listen to me.

316
00:22:58,200 --> 00:23:01,733
What exactly are you going to
say to erase what you did wrong?

317
00:23:02,133 --> 00:23:04,733
I can't change what I've done.

318
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:11,100
But I want to make things right,
Marj.

319
00:23:11,233 --> 00:23:12,867
Right?

320
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:13,967
How?

321
00:23:15,433 --> 00:23:17,567
I'll talk to Regina.

322
00:23:19,333 --> 00:23:22,000
I'll admit to her what happened.

323
00:23:22,167 --> 00:23:24,633
Mom, are you serious?

324
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:26,233
She'll kill you.

325
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:29,600
I know, Marj.

326
00:23:29,733 --> 00:23:32,833
But I'll accept if she hurts me.

327
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:37,533
It's better if she hears it
from me than from someone else.

328
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:43,833
Ma'am?

329
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:45,967
Ma'am?

330
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:47,733
Are you okay?

331
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:52,600
Oh, Yolly...

332
00:23:52,733 --> 00:23:54,467
It's happening again.

333
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,800
Greg's cheating again.

334
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:03,733
He hasn't grown wiser with age,
right?

335
00:24:05,300 --> 00:24:10,333
He's in his 60s and
still not satisfied with life.

336
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:12,967
And the funny part?

337
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:15,967
There are still women
falling for him.

338
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:19,433
But I'm sure, Yolly,
it's just about the money.

339
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:22,333
Do you know who she is, Ma'am?

340
00:24:22,467 --> 00:24:23,833
I wish I did, Yolly.

341
00:24:23,967 --> 00:24:27,233
So I'd know how low
Greg's standards have gone.

342
00:24:32,667 --> 00:24:34,000
Yolly!

343
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,833
That's the gift for that
mistress!

344
00:24:37,967 --> 00:24:39,333
Don't tell me, Yolly!

345
00:24:39,467 --> 00:24:42,067
I'll apologize to her,

346
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:47,333
even though what I did
is unforgivable.

347
00:24:50,033 --> 00:24:52,567
I understand...

348
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:55,733
if you, too, can't forgive me,
dear.

349
00:24:57,400 --> 00:25:02,433
I know I've only brought
problems to you.

350
00:25:04,233 --> 00:25:08,100
Mom, I didn't mean
to tell you that.

351
00:25:08,367 --> 00:25:10,367
But you need to know.

352
00:25:10,500 --> 00:25:12,233
But still, Marj.

353
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:16,200
So I promise you,

354
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:21,667
even if it costs me everything,

355
00:25:21,967 --> 00:25:23,867
I'll make it up to you, Marj.

356
00:25:29,133 --> 00:25:30,133
Mom.

357
00:25:31,467 --> 00:25:32,467
Mom.

358
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:35,100
I'll be with you.

359
00:25:39,833 --> 00:25:41,967
Oh no, Ma'am, this isn't mine.

360
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:44,533
I just saw it
among Ma'am Evelyn's things.

361
00:25:47,633 --> 00:25:48,900
Among...

362
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:53,400
Evelyn's things?

363
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,900
Regina, please forgive me.

364
00:26:10,067 --> 00:26:11,767
Can we talk?

365
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:13,367
Don't call me that.

366
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:17,100
We're ending this.
Right here, right now.

367
00:26:17,233 --> 00:26:19,233
If you really
are breaking up with me,

368
00:26:19,367 --> 00:26:21,600
at least grant me this one
request.

369
00:26:21,733 --> 00:26:23,167
Let's do it.

370
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:26,000
Seriously, Marj,
this is all your fault.

371
00:26:26,133 --> 00:26:28,967
Your mom's embarrassing.

372
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:32,500
She's old, and still flirting.

373
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:34,633
Dad, is this true?

374
00:26:34,767 --> 00:26:36,800
She was the one flirting
with me.

375
00:26:36,933 --> 00:26:38,267
I am the victim here.

376
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,233
I know you are
your dad's favorite.

377
00:26:40,367 --> 00:26:44,833
Don't be as evil
as your father, please.

378
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,933
Jobert has a new video.

379
00:26:50,333 --> 00:26:52,167
Good grief!

380
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,367
This house is a pig pen!

381
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:59,067
Because you brought two pigs
under one roof!
